## 6. Implementation Order

1. **`app/globals.css`** — Theme transitions (CSS only, lowest risk)
2. **`kpi-bar.tsx`** — KPI entrance + count-up
3. **`widgets-section.tsx`** — Micro-interactions + entrance
4. **`cases-modal.tsx`** — AnimatePresence + modal content animation
5. **`modal-table.tsx`** — Row stagger + hover CSS class

---

## 7. Risks & Mitigations

| Risk | Likelihood | Mitigation |
|------|------------|------------|
| Tailwind `@apply` purging | High | Use raw CSS instead of `@apply` for transitions |
| Radix + framer-motion conflict | Medium | Wrap children only, not DialogContent |
| CSS var runtime resolution in whileHover | High | Use hardcoded HSL values for table hover |
| Animation performance jank | Low | Use only `transform`/`opacity`; avoid layout triggers |
| prefers-reduced-motion not respected | Medium | Explicit check via `useReducedMotion()` hook |

---

## 8. Rollback Plan

1. Remove CSS transition from `app/globals.css`
2. Remove `motion.div` wrappers from KPI bar, widgets, modal
3. Remove `AnimatePresence` from cases-modal
4. Replace `motion.tr` with plain `TableRow` in modal-table
5. Remove `.table-row-hover` CSS class from globals.css

